docs.text: Welcome to the Lab Template This repo can be used as a starting point for new labs. It leverages MKDocs to generate static HTML that can be published to Github Pages . For full documentation visit mkdocs.org . You are currently viewing the github pages site for this repo. To see the actual repo click on the Github link in the lower left corner of the browser, at the bottom of the left navigation menu. Note This is an example of a component of the admonition extension. You can learn more about options for this component here . Tip This is what a markdown link looks like: [MKDocs](https://www.mkdocs.org) This link renders like this: MKDocs One of the issues with markdown is that it does not support links that open in new windows or tabs. Markdown does support regular HTML, so you could also do that same link like this: MKDocs This one renders like this: MKDocs
